name: Michael Rodriguez
title: Senior Real Estate Agent
bio: Michael brings over 15 years of real estate experience to the Treasure Coast market. Specializing in luxury homes and waterfront properties, he has consistently ranked among the top performers in the region. His deep knowledge of local neighborhoods and market trends, combined with his commitment to exceptional client service, has earned him a reputation as one of the most trusted agents in the area.
serviceArea: Vero Beach, Sebastian, Indian River County

name: Sarah Chen
title: Commercial Real Estate Specialist
bio: Sarah specializes in commercial real estate transactions and investment properties throughout the Treasure Coast. With a background in finance and extensive market knowledge, she helps clients identify profitable investment opportunities and navigate complex commercial deals. Her analytical approach and attention to detail ensure successful outcomes for both buyers and sellers.
serviceArea: Treasure Coast, Martin County, St. Lucie County

name: David Thompson
title: Property Management Director
bio: David oversees our property management division with over 20 years of experience in rental property management and real estate investment. He manages a portfolio of over 500 units and specializes in maximizing rental income while maintaining high occupancy rates. His expertise includes tenant relations, maintenance coordination, and investment property analysis.

name: Jennifer Martinez
title: Residential Sales Agent
bio: Jennifer is passionate about helping families find their perfect home on the Treasure Coast. With a focus on first-time homebuyers and growing families, she provides patient guidance throughout the entire buying process. Her bilingual abilities and cultural sensitivity make her an excellent choice for diverse clientele in our multicultural community.
serviceArea: Port St. Lucie, Fort Pierce, Stuart

name: Robert Johnson
title: Development Consultant
bio: Robert leads our development consulting division with extensive experience in real estate development, zoning, and project management. He has successfully guided over 50 development projects from conception to completion, specializing in residential subdivisions and commercial developments. His expertise in municipal relations and entitlement processes is invaluable for complex projects.

name: Lisa Anderson
title: Real Estate School Director
bio: Lisa oversees our real estate education programs and has been instrumental in training hundreds of successful real estate professionals. With her extensive teaching background and real estate expertise, she ensures our students receive comprehensive, up-to-date education that prepares them for successful careers in real estate.
